  "prompt": "How do I get my company's website on the first page of Google?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies to improve your website's Google ranking:\n\n1. Search Engine Optimization (SEO)\n- Use relevant keywords\n- Optimize page titles and meta descriptions\n- Create high-quality, original content\n- Ensure mobile-friendly design\n- Improve website loading speed\n\n2. Content Marketing\n- Publish regular, valuable blog posts\n- Create informative articles\n- Use long-tail keywords\n- Update content consistently\n\n3. Technical SEO\n- Ensure proper website structure\n- Create XML sitemap\n- Use header tags correctly\n- Implement schema markup\n- Fix broken links\n\n4. Link Building\n- Get backlinks from reputable websites\n- Create shareable content\n- Guest post on industry blogs\n- Use social media to promote content\n\n5. Local SEO (for local businesses)\n- Claim Google My Business listing\n- Get local citations\n- Encourage customer reviews\n- Include local keywords\n\n6. Google Ads\n- Run targeted pay-per-click campaigns\n- Use relevant ad copy and keywords\n\n7. Track Progress\n- Use Google Analytics\n- Monitor search rankings\n- Adjust strategy based on performance\n\nRemember, SEO is an ongoing process that requires consistent effort and adaptation.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these strategies?",
